description:
The Human Tissue Squad

Two-part documentary following the work of the tissue-donation team at Liverpool's national human tissue bank, and the experiences of some of the patients to whom it provides life-saving transplants.

In the first edition, the team battles a shortage of tissue supplies while attempting to cope with demand from hospitals nationwide, and tries to find a donor shin bone for 19-year-old Morgan.

The second in a two-part documentary following the work of the tissue-donation team at Liverpool's national human tissue bank, and the experiences of some of the patients to whom it provides life-saving transplants. In this edition, 18-year-old Reuben requires a life-changing operation on a tumour in his knee, and the emotional strain begins to take its toll on specialist nurse Laura.
